1
00:00:07,133 --> 00:00:10,643
Now Freud tells us
everyone in this world

2
00:00:10,657 --> 00:00:14,533
is bewildered 
by the erotic principle.

3
00:00:14,533 --> 00:00:18,267
That’s what’s driving 
all of existence.

4
00:00:18,397 --> 00:00:20,652
[Erotic Principle]

5
00:00:21,315 --> 00:00:22,972
And in this sense

6
00:00:22,972 --> 00:00:28,565
he’s stumbled upon
a very essential principle.

7
00:00:28,565 --> 00:00:32,381
He’s saying the sexual principle
is driving everything;

8
00:00:32,381 --> 00:00:35,465
it’s driving the ants,
it’s driving the human beings,

9
00:00:35,472 --> 00:00:38,090
love makes the world 
go ’round.

10
00:00:40,495 --> 00:00:44,521
It’s the force
that’s behind everything.
 

11
00:00:45,385 --> 00:00:49,447
And he has his system
of interpretation for that.

12
00:00:49,447 --> 00:00:51,965
But see, 
what he’s expressing

13
00:00:51,965 --> 00:00:56,399
is a perverted reflection 
of the truth.
 

14
00:00:56,399 --> 00:00:59,122
The erotic principle, expressed

15
00:00:59,122 --> 00:01:02,478
in unalloyed devotion
in the spiritual world,
 

16
00:01:02,478 --> 00:01:04,894
that’s the source 
of everything.

17
00:01:04,894 --> 00:01:07,727
The loving relationship
between Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa

18
00:01:07,727 --> 00:01:09,470
is the source 
of everything,

19
00:01:09,470 --> 00:01:12,730
and this world is
a perverted reflection of that.

20
00:01:12,730 --> 00:01:15,121
So Freud was right 
in identifying:

21
00:01:15,121 --> 00:01:21,071
this is what’s driving everything
in the world, is the erotic principle.

22
00:01:22,223 --> 00:01:26,621
And what the spiritual experts
are saying,

23
00:01:26,621 --> 00:01:31,757
in its unalloyed unconditional
pure expression,

24
00:01:31,757 --> 00:01:36,690
it’s what’s driving everything
in the spiritual world.
 

25
00:01:36,690 --> 00:01:42,404
So naturally what he’s saying
is true here,

26
00:01:42,404 --> 00:01:44,455
because in the Supreme Reality,

27
00:01:44,455 --> 00:01:48,370
it’s the source, it’s the origin,
it’s driving everything.

28
00:01:48,370 --> 00:01:52,347
And in the place where it’s perverted,
similarly,

29
00:01:52,347 --> 00:01:59,231
but, in the words Saraswatī Ṭhākur uses
sometimes, it’s “vitiated”.

30
00:01:59,231 --> 00:02:04,211
Rather than it being wholesome
and pure and nourishing,

31
00:02:04,211 --> 00:02:09,322
it’s degrading.

32
00:02:09,786 --> 00:02:12,687
So Freud identified:
everyone in the world

33
00:02:12,687 --> 00:02:18,153
is under the influence of 
Cupid, Madan.
 

34
00:02:18,153 --> 00:02:24,190
Madan Mohan means
the seductive charm,

35
00:02:24,190 --> 00:02:27,255
attraction, sweetness, 
of Kṛṣṇa,

36
00:02:27,255 --> 00:02:32,296
is capable of bewildering Cupid.
 

37
00:02:32,296 --> 00:02:37,111
Everyone here bewildered by Cupid,
Cupid bewildered by Kṛṣṇa.

38
00:02:37,111 --> 00:02:39,060
But by extension,
what it means is

39
00:02:39,060 --> 00:02:41,797
everyone who’s bewildered by Cupid

40
00:02:41,797 --> 00:02:46,307
can overcome that bewilderment, 
illusion,

41
00:02:46,307 --> 00:02:57,277
by redirecting this innate
intrinsic principle towards Kṛṣṇā.

42
00:02:57,309 --> 00:03:02,452
Kṛṣṇa can fulfil—
if we take that principle
 

43
00:03:02,452 --> 00:03:05,102
to its highest level
of fulfilment and expression—

44
00:03:05,102 --> 00:03:08,726
he alone can fulfil that. 
Kṛṣṇa.

